liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: Theres still no decision in New Jersey, where the count is close and the data is murky. But county by county, its becoming clear that there are still a lot of Democratic-leaning mail ballots left. That might be enough for Murphy.

liveUpdates.author: Blake Hounshell
liveUpdates.text: President Biden just touched down at Joint Base Andrews after his trip to Rome and Glasgow, returning from the rarified heights of foreign summitry to a sour, gridlocked Washington riven with Democratic infighting.

liveUpdates.author: Jennifer Medina
liveUpdates.text: In his victory speech, Youngkin focused once again on schools, promising choice within the public school system and curriculum that teaches children how to think. Education, mixed with race, became one of the most salient issues in the campaign.

liveUpdates.author: Jennifer Medina
liveUpdates.text: Youngkin was the big story in Virginia, but the statealso elected its first Black woman lieutenant governor and its first Latino attorney general, both Republicans.

liveUpdates.author: Tracey Tully
liveUpdates.text: Phil Murphy, New Jerseys Democratic governor, and his Republican challenger, Jack Ciattarelli, addressed supporters almost simultaneously early Wednesday. Both said it will take more time to count all the vote-by-mail and provisional ballots.

liveUpdates.author: Neil Vigdor
liveUpdates.text: The World Series ends  and so have the mayoral ambitions of Bobby Valentine, who concedes to Democrat Caroline Simmons in Stamford, Conn.

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: As Democrats try and make sense of the wreckage tonight, one fact stands out as one of the easiest explanations: Joe Biden has lower approval ratings at this stage of his presidency than nearly any president in the era of modern polling.

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: An example of the difficulty in New Jersey is Bergen County, where Republicans may  or may not  be on track to hold on to their lead. One election document says they've counted heavily Democratic mail votes; another says they haven't.

liveUpdates.author: Timothy Arango
liveUpdates.text: Minneapolis' rejection of a referendum to replace their police department will not end the conversation over reforming law enforcement there. Voters largely agreed that policing needs to change. They were less sure about how to do it.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Jenn Ackerman for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Jeremy W. Peters
liveUpdates.text: In the reddest part of Virginia, its southwestern coal country, Youngkin is getting a slightly higher percentage of the vote than Trump did in several counties in 2020. 80-85+ percent tonight.

liveUpdates.author: Richard Fausset
liveUpdates.text: In Atlanta, front-runner Felicia Moore, the city council president and a longtime critic of former mayor Kasim Reed, will advance to a runoff. But Mr. Reed and councilman Andre Dickens are fighting for the No. 2 spot.

liveUpdates.author: Reid Epstein
liveUpdates.text: In Great Falls, Mont., Mayor Bob Kelly cruised to re-election over his challenger, Fred Burow. Mr. Kelly is a supporter of the local effort to create a National Heritage Area. Mr. Burrow has opposed the proposal and trumpeted disinformation about it.

liveUpdates.author: Dana Rubinstein
liveUpdates.text: Brad Lander will be New York Citys next comptroller, according to the AP. He and his ally, Public Advocate Jumaane Williams, are are expected to form a left-leaning coalition, possibly in opposition to Mayor-elect Eric Adams, who is closer to the political center.

liveUpdates.author: Richard Fausset
liveUpdates.text: Historic night in Durham, N.C., where Elaine ONeal, a former interim dean of N.C. Central University Law School, will become the citys first Black woman mayor.

liveUpdates.author: Patricia Mazzei
liveUpdates.text: In the Democratic primary for Floridas 20th Congressional District, Sheila Cherfilus-McCormick leads Dale Holness by a mere 31 votes. That would trigger an automatic recount for the heavily Democratic seat in Broward and Palm Beach counties.

liveUpdates.author: Tracey Tully
liveUpdates.text: Diane Allen, Jack Ciattarellis Republican running-mate in New Jersey, just addressed an energized G.O.P. crowd watching results arrive slowly. We feel good, she said. Lets continue.

liveUpdates.author: Kendrick Brinson
liveUpdates.text: Felicia Moore, a candidate for mayor in Atlanta, hugged supporters at her election night watch party in Downtown Atlanta.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Kendrick Brinson for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Reid Epstein
liveUpdates.text: Terry McAuliffe, who did not concede defeat in his brief remarks, will not be speaking again tonight, an aide said.

liveUpdates.author: Reid Epstein
liveUpdates.text: McAuliffe in a speech before supporters: We still got a lot of vote to count, we have about 18 percent of the vote out, we're going to continue to count the votes because every single Virginian deserves to have their vote counted.

liveUpdates.author: Doug Mills
liveUpdates.text: Terry McAuliffe supporters looked concerned while watching a big screen showing early returns at a watch party in Fairfax.

liveUpdates.author: Timothy Arango
liveUpdates.text: The failed referendum to replace the Minneapolis Police Department with a new public safety agency reflected a generational divide within the citys Black community. Younger activists pushed for it. Some older leaders said it was too much of a gamble.

liveUpdates.author: Bryan Anselm
liveUpdates.text: Supporters of New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy have gathered at a party on the boardwalk in Asbury Park to watch the results come in.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Bryan Anselm for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: Democrats may be poised for big disappointment in Virginia, but they do seem likely to hold on in New Jersey  even though the Republican leads at the moment. Virtually all the reported vote is from Republican areas.

liveUpdates.author: Richard Fausset
liveUpdates.text: Youngkins showing tonight is of interest to two possible Georgia governors candidates, Democrat Stacey Abrams and Republican David Perdue  who, like Youngkin, might seek to unite pro- and anti-Trump G.O.P. factions.

liveUpdates.author: Dana Rubinstein
liveUpdates.text: Alvin Bragg will become Manhattans first Black district attorney, according to the Associated Press. He will inherit a high-profile case against former President Donald J. Trump.

liveUpdates.author: Jeff Mays
liveUpdates.text: We won, shouted an Eric Adams staffer from the stage just 17 minutes after the polls closed in New York City.

liveUpdates.author: Dana Rubinstein
liveUpdates.text: The polls have closed in New York City. We will know the outcome of the mayors race, and several down-ballot races, soon.

liveUpdates.author: Jeremy W. Peters
liveUpdates.text: If Youngkin prevails, expect the two warring factions of the G.O.P. to both declare victory. "Never Trumpers" will claim this shows theres a path without him. And Trump supporters will say he dragged Youngkin over the line.

liveUpdates.author: Shane Goldmacher
liveUpdates.text: McAuliffe is far underperforming his 2013 showing in rural and white parts of southwestern Virginia by as much as 20 percentage points in some places.

liveUpdates.author: Melissa Lyttle
liveUpdates.text: Mike Stoddard of Herndon, Va., watching results on a big screen at a Glenn Youngkin watch party in Chantilly: Financially, emotionally, spiritually, I think hes just trying to get veterans and Virginians back on track.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Melissa Lyttle for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Jeremy W. Peters
liveUpdates.text: In heavily blue Fairfax County, the early and absentee results so far, roughly 75-25 for McAuliffe, is where Republicans think they need to be if this is going to be close.

liveUpdates.author: Timothy Arango
liveUpdates.text: In Minneapolis, Democrats are divided over a charter amendment to replace the Police Department. Progressives  like Rep. Ilhan Omar  have been vocal in support. Moderates like Sen. Amy Klobuchar oppose the measure but have not campaigned against it.

liveUpdates.author: Reid Epstein
liveUpdates.text: In Lexington, Va., where Joe Biden won 65 percent of the vote, Terry McAuliffe is at just 50 percent with about half the vote counted so far. Its a good representation of how far behind Biden McAuliffe is running in tonights results.

liveUpdates.author: Doug Mills
liveUpdates.text: At a watch party for Terry McAuliffe in in Fairfax, Va., supporters checked their laptops to see the early return numbers.

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: McAuliffe is ever so slightly underperforming. The latest example is Fairfax: McAuliffe is at 74 percent of the advance vote, but our estimate was that he needed 76 percent. Its early and not much, but its starting to add up.

liveUpdates.author: Tracey Tully
liveUpdates.text: Gov. Phil Murphys supporters are filing into Asbury Parks Convention Hall in New Jersey, the same place he celebrated his 2017 win.

liveUpdates.author: Tracey Tully
liveUpdates.text: A judge rejected a request to keep polls open in New Jersey until 9:30 p.m. He said it would cause disarray, and theres no proof that voters were turned away because of snags with the new electronic poll books.

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: Youngkin has an early lead in Virginia. That may be deceptive. So far, we mainly have heavily Republican Election Day vote. Over all, 12 percent of Election Day votes have been counted by the state, compared to just 5 percent of early and 2 percent of absentee votes.

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: Its early, but so far more than 100 precincts have reported in Virginia and theyre generally consistent with a highly competitive race with a very high turnout.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Melissa Lyttle for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Richard Fausset
liveUpdates.text: In Atlanta, a runoff is likely in this crowded mayors race. Mayor Kasim Reed and council president Felicia Moore have polled well. A wildcard: Andre Dickens, a critic of Reeds.

liveUpdates.author: Trip Gabriel
liveUpdates.text: Democratic strategists in Chesterfield County last week told me they did not expect McAuliffe to win there, even though Biden carried the traditionally conservative region.

liveUpdates.author: Jeff Mays
liveUpdates.text: All is quiet here at the New York Marriott where Eric Adams is set to hold his election night party. I think were going to win, joked one adviser to the likely next mayor.

liveUpdates.author: Jennifer Medina
liveUpdates.text: Republicans tried to make critical race theory a central part of the Virginia governors race, but parents anger over schools may have had more to do with pandemic shutdowns.

liveUpdates.author: Reid Epstein
liveUpdates.text: Fairfax is usually among Virginias last counties to report final results in statewide elections and has in past elections given Democratic candidates a boost at the end of election nights.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Kenny Holston for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Reid Epstein
liveUpdates.text: Fairfax County is delayed in reporting its early vote ballots. We do not know when we are expecting those ballots to be counted, but it will not be by the self-imposed 8 p.m. deadline.

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: For Youngkin to win, hes going to need it all: a favorable turnout and gains across the state. But there are two big counties he all but must flip back: Virginia Beach and Chesterfield, outside Richmond.

liveUpdates.author: Shane Goldmacher
liveUpdates.text: In the final tally, $66.3 million was spent on television ads in the Virginia governors race general election, according to AdImpact. Democrats spent more: $34.6 million to $31.7 million.

liveUpdates.author: Richard Fausset
liveUpdates.text: In Atlanta, the focus is on former Mayor Kasim Reed, a familiar figure burdened by his administrations scandals. The question is whether his high name recognition will trump high negatives.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Kendrick Brinson for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: Democrats might jump to an early lead in Virginia, where counties are now allowed to pre-process absentee votes. That should allow for quick reporting of votes that are expected to be heavily Democratic.

liveUpdates.author: Dana Rubinstein
liveUpdates.text: Polls close in New York City in about two hours. Anecdotally, turnout appears low, which is unlikely to affect the outcome of the mayors race. But it could affect some down-ballot contests.

liveUpdates.author: Timothy Arango
liveUpdates.text: Minneapolis recorded the most homicides since the mid-1990s last year. As voters weigh whether to replace the city's police department, many are caught between two beliefs  that policing needs to be drastically reformed, and that more policing is needed to confront the surge in gun violence.

liveUpdates.author: Ellen Barry
liveUpdates.text: Many Boston voters cited the need for affordable housing. A lot of people realize they wont be able to live in this city in 10 years if this continues, said Andrew Conant, 28.

liveUpdates.author: Jennifer Medina
liveUpdates.text: When voting began this morning, nearly 1.2 million Virginians had already cast ballots. By comparison, 2.6 million voters turned out in 2017, the last time the state picked its governor.

liveUpdates.author: Shane Goldmacher
liveUpdates.text: There are several interesting mayors races nationwide that pit more progressive versus more moderate Democrats, including in Boston, Seattle, Cleveland, Minneapolis and Buffalo

liveUpdates.author: Timothy Arango
liveUpdates.text: Minneapolis will decide whether to keep or replace its long-troubled Police Department. Im interested to see returns in North Minneapolis, which has high rates of gun violence and where many people want more police.

liveUpdates.author: Trip Gabriel
liveUpdates.text: In Richmond, Va., a deep blue city, voters found many ways to say theyre nervous: Im really on pins and needles. I was hoping wed be up by a higher margin. My anxiety level is high.

liveUpdates.author: Tracey Tully
liveUpdates.text: Concerns about voter turnout in New Jersey already had both campaigns for governor in overdrive. Then there were reports of tech snags that led to lines of frustrated voters.

liveUpdates.author: Jeremy W. Peters
liveUpdates.text: Youngkin has managed to keep Trump at an arms length. If he wins, Never Trump Republicans and moderates will argue that Virginia is their new template. And Trump will likely claim victory.

liveUpdates.author: Nate Cohn
liveUpdates.text: There are signs of high turnout in Virginia, but not many clues about who may benefit. High turnout is assumed to help Democrats, but Republicans stand to gain if more white, working class voters go to the polls.

liveUpdates.author: Astead W. Herndon
liveUpdates.text: An old enemy is threatening the final hours of voting in Virginia: weather. Officials are eyeing increasing chances of rain and lightning in some of the states metro areas.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Melissa Lyttle for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Dana Rubinstein
liveUpdates.text: The contest between Eric Adams and Curtis Sliwa is something of a fait accompli. In New York City, where Democrats far outnumber Republicans, Adams is expected to win. The question is, by how much.

liveUpdates.author: Ellen Barry
liveUpdates.text: Progressives in Boston have been galvanized by Michelle Wus ambitious proposals, like rent control and fare-free public transit. But other voters expressed skepticism that Wu could deliver, and said this has swayed them to Annissa Essaibi George. I know Michelle believes she can do all these things, said Edward Ake, 48, an immigrant from Cameroon. But its not going to happen. Im sorry to say it so bluntly.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Philip Keith for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Ellen Barry
liveUpdates.text: Boston will elect a woman to be mayor for the first time. The candidates are city councilors Annissa Essaibi George, a former schoolteacher, and Michelle Wu, who has galvanized young progressives.
liveUpdates.image_credit: Philip Keith for The New York Times

liveUpdates.author: Jeff Mays
liveUpdates.text: New York City residents are poised to elect Eric Adams as the second Black mayor and Alvin Bragg as the first Black district attorney of Manhattan. Follow our updates.
